<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[This Regulation is prescribed in accordance with Military Education Regulation, the Nineteenth Clause ,Rule One.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Army Infantry School (AIS) is subordinated to the ministry of National Defense (MND),could be authorized to act the founding of the school by Army Command Headquarters ,MND.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The objective of the AIS is to train  Army officer and sergeant's field infantry, armored infantry, and maintenance speciality.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The further education of the AIS is designed in accordance with school's features and policies.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 5</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The AACS is departmentalized into divisions, centers, and offices, each of which being in charge of the following items ,and divide into groups to wield in purpose.
（1）Academic Section: in charge of enrolment, register, curriculum affairs, teaching materials, student status, and other academic affairs.
（2）Students' Affairs Section: in charge of Psychological counseling, life counseling, health care, extracurricular activities guidance, patriotic education, counseling service, military discipline,ethics and military security.
（3）General Affairs Section: in charge of personnel, logistics, construction, and other general affairs.
（4）Training Division: in charge of training, supervision, evaluation, and enforcement of intelligence and operational training, armored corps garrison training and evaluation, armored corps Base Training and evaluation.
（5）Information Library Center: in charge of collection of teaching research resources, and providing inform service. developing information system and personnel training.
（6）Comptroller Office: in charge of budgeting, general accounting, and statistics.
（7）Operation Research and Development Office: in charge of publishing of Army infantry and armored infantry manning and equipping, doctrines, material research and development, military academic journals, and other operational research developments.
（8）General Instructor Office: in charge of planning lessons and training executing of military training and physical techniques.
Any organizational change or extension for teaching, research, and recruitment could only be made under the ratification of the MND.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 6</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The AIS consists of Student Brigade, Training and Service Battalion, and Headquarter Company.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 7</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The AIS has one principal , Major General and in charge of general school affairs. There are one vice principal, one Executive Director and one Director of Political Warfare, all of them are Colonel responsible for assisting the principal in dealing with school affairs.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 8</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Deleted
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 9</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The official rank and prescribed number of personnel listed in the Regulation is specified by the Table of Organization.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 10</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The AIS is not allowed to hire employees after the Regulations executed in May 22,2007.Each of hired employees keep working until out of duty.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 11</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The Regulation shall be implemented upon its officialization.
]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
